    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Process or technique of covering a dried painted surface with a thin coat of a different transparent color, usually in order to modify the tone without mixing. To cover with a transparent varnish for protection, use "varnishing."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
